I got in front of the camera this year more than I ever have in my boudoir photography career and I’m not mad at it. 

When we say you will come back for more, we are not kidding. Boudoir IS addicting— After you see yourself through someone else’s eyes you appreciate all the things that you nit pick about yourself.

This post is for everyone who keeps coming at me in the anonymous box (because you won’t dare say it to my face) about the plus size comments. 

I have NEVER turned away a client because of what size they are. 
Posing can make it appear as if someone is a completely different size, so a lot of times there is someone who is considered to be plus sized and you cannot tell from the angle, the lighting, or the pose. 
My client closet ranges from XS-5X because again we include everyone and believe that you should have a boudoir experience no matter what the number on the scale or your jean size says. 
I do not body alter any of my clients meaning I do not cinch your waist or take away pounds off anyone (much like many other boudoir photographers that I know do) 
I shoot with just as many plus size women as I do small ones. I only share the images that clients allow me to and fully respect my clients decisions when they don’t want to share. 
I provide the same luxury experience for EVERY BODY, ask any of my past clients. 

So please, if you do not like what you see on my feed, see your way out. I am tired of the back handed comments. They are uncalled for. 
And unless you are willing to step in front of my camera and actually share your images for others to see then respectfully you have no room to talk. 

As always thank you to those who back me up on this and have trusted my experience as a photographer to create beautiful images for you and not used my size as a reason not to book with me ❤️

Real talk: there will ALWAYS be more work to do.

Yup… there will. 

Work is never ending. 

There will ALWAYS be ONE more DM to answer, caption to write, email to respond to, photo to edit, meeting to pop into, blog post to write, reel to film. That work will ALWAYS be there.

But you know what there won't be more of?

Time TODAY to spend with your family. These years and days are so precious & if we're not careful we'll completely miss them in our hustle for more money, more followers, more features, more notoriety.

As you’re working around the clock, trying to get ALL the things done on your list… remember WHY you are doing all of this in the first place. Remember WHO matters most in this moment. Is it the person you hardly know on Instagram? Or is it your little girl wanting so badly to play? Is it your husband looking forward to that unplugged time during dinner? Is it your grandma hoping to pick up the phone and chat because it’s been a while?

Because I PROMISE… it’s not that ONE more DM you have to send!

“I’m only one person, so what difference will I make?” is something I hear often...

It’s the notion that we’re only a small speck in the great mechanism of humanity. But really, that couldn’t be further from the truth. 🙅🏼‍♀️⁣
⁣
I’m understanding this more everyday… sometimes it hits in the most random of places.⁣
⁣
A couple of weeks ago while catching some sun pool side, I considered hopping in, with the temperature as the one true deciding factor. 💦👙☀️⁣
⁣
As I dipped my toes in to test the water, I observed how perfectly calm it looked. But after disturbing the surface... I noticed ALL the waves in the form of rings, very small at first, then ever expanding + increasing in number until they spread across the whole pool: the ripple effect in action.⁣
⁣
I sat there for a moment in awe of this simple reminder... we create our OWN ripple effects to those around us every day. ⁣
⁣
Think about it... how many people do you see on the daily? In our daily lives, we affect hundreds, if not THOUSANDS, of people in BIG ways, ways we may NEVER quite understand. Isn’t it wonderful + terrifying all at the same time?!⁣
⁣
Because if we’re not taking the opportunity to brighten someone’s day and exemplifying love/patience... then we’re doing the opposite. There’s so much we’re responsible for: impacting someone’s day with love and joy… or the opposite. YIKES.
⁣
Don’t underestimate the ripple effect of your actions. Don’t underestimate your impact on the people around you. You have influence. You have the power to CHANGE THE WORLD. 🌎⁣
⁣
👉🏼 Be kind.⁣
👉🏼 Treat others with love and respect.⁣
👉🏼 Choose joy.⁣
⁣
Every word that you speak, every action you make affects other people. They DO have an impact... they impact your coworker in the cubicle next to you, that barista from Starbucks that makes your coffee every morning or that bus driver that drives you to work everyday. 👩🏽‍💻☕️🚃 Take those opportunities to their day brighter. ✨⁣

Often times I know this phrase is just used because it’s something people just say. While it’s understandable that glimpses of peoples lives on social media can seem like they’re “living it up”, it disregards the immense dedication, late nights, and relentless determination that paved the path to success. Rather than dismissing it as mere luck or a stroke of fortune, I want you to put yourself in that persons shoes and recognize that success is rarely an overnight achievement. Behind every snapshot of contentment lies a story of sacrifices, set backs, and unyielding commitment. We can change the narrative and shift away from envy by embracing a spirit of admiration, drawing inspiration from the journey that led to these moments of fulfillment. You can celebrate the achievements of others while remembering the toil that led them there— it’s about nurturing a culture of empathy and support instead of passing judgement with a fleeting glance.

Happy Monday! It's that fantastic time of the year again when we celebrate the incredible contributions of Hispanic and Latinx communities in the USA. Getting ready for your boudoir photoshoot can be both thrilling and a little nerve-wracking, right? Well, I'm here to guide you through it, girlfriend! Here are some things you need to leave behind before walking through my studio doors:

Insecurities and Self-Doubt:
We all have our insecurities, but guess what? Your photographer's got your back. Trust their pro skills to capture your absolute best angles.

Expectation of Perfection:
Boudoir is all about embracing our unique beauty. So, leave the pressure to be "perfect" behind. Trust that your photographer will make you shine.

Packed Wardrobe:
You know that thing where you want to bring your whole closet? Not here, hun! Trust your photographer's fashion sense and go with the flow.

Negative Energy or Stress:
There is no room for harsh self criticism here! Trust that your photographer will set the mood for a relaxed and empowering experience. Trust your photographer to lift you up and keep those positive vibes rolling.

Specific Poses or Pinterest Expectations:
We all love Pinterest, but let's not get stuck on someone else's ideas. Trust your photographer's creative genius to guide you through it.

Need for Immediate Perfection:
We all want things ASAP, but hold up a sec. Trust the editing process – perfection takes time. You're worth the wait.

In the world of boudoir, trust is our BFF. Ditch the insecurities and perfectionism. Trust your photographer for a mind-blowing journey, capturing your unique beauty. Embrace this adventure with trust and DM me to book today <3

So why settle for something when you can embrace the true vulnerability of boudoir? Now dont get it twisted im not forcing anyones hand to go full spicy noodle but at least try that spicy wardrobe.
